                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/436.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">La Union, Salvador,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 19, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that the Salvadorean minister for foreign affairs states that the
                    condition of anarchy in Honduras justifies Salvador in maintaining forces on the
                    frontier as a measure of self-defense. Also reports that the peace negotiations
                    are not yet concluded, but that he is hopeful, provided the revolution against
                    Salvador is suppressed. Adds that the attitude of Nicaragua on this point is not
                    at all clear.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
